Use `fs.promises.access`, which resolves on existence and rejects on absence — wrap in a try/catch and treat any rejection as 'not found':

```ts
import fs from "fs/promises";

async function fileExists(path: string): Promise<boolean> {
  try {
    await fs.access(path);
    return true;
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

Do NOT use the older `fs.exists` callback — it's been deprecated for years because of TOCTOU race issues. The `access` pattern is the canonical replacement.
